<span id="freeTextContainer12647306963782998577">A superb, absorbing story of a surgeon, under training. I read this book first time long back, when I, myself, was a doctor/surgeon in the making. It had a great influence on me at that time. Now, when I am re-reading this book after almost 35-40 years later, it looks so interesting and inspiring. The wit and honesty of the narration makes you laugh and cry at the same time. The stories are informative, poignant and often funny. Dr Nolen has been very honest, forthright and unpretentious in tell</span>
  <span id="freeText12647306963782998577" style="display:none">A superb, absorbing story of a surgeon, under training. I read this book first time long back, when I, myself, was a doctor/surgeon in the making. It had a great influence on me at that time. Now, when I am re-reading this book after almost 35-40 years later, it looks so interesting and inspiring. The wit and honesty of the narration makes you laugh and cry at the same time. The stories are informative, poignant and often funny. Dr Nolen has been very honest, forthright and unpretentious in telling the stories in the life of a training surgeon in a public hospital in NewYork. I enjoyed it immensely and will recommend it to everyone.</span>
