<span id="freeTextContainer248937364925344333">I am a surgical resident and I wish I read this book earlier. It is an amazing tale of the training of a surgeon in a busy public hospital in NYC during the 50s and 60s. Compared to surgical training today, so much is different and yet so much is the same. A fascinating read and a book I will recommend to every medical student interested in surgery. </span>

          </span>
