              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9375633009152873814">This book is the autobiography of William A. Nolan, and his struggle through medical school at the Bellevue public hospital in New York. This book is extremely funny as well as informative of the process of becoming a doctor. He explores the challenges and joys of working in a hospital, as well as the emotional strain he experienced. I would recommend this book to anyone who is even remotely interested in medicine, but especially to anyone who is seriously considering becoming a doctor/ surgeon.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


